      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tapering off warfarin without medical supervision is dangerous. If you want to transition, do it under a doctor's supervision, not on your own. They can help you adjust your diet and supplements safely. But remember, no amount of natural remedies can replace the careful balance warfarin provides. Stay safe, and don't try to play doctor with your health.",
